last stop.tips: Prioritize a good sniper as gem carrier in middle. In bushes you can run an anti agro, assassin, or brawler good at scouting.

triple dribble.tips: Thrower heavy draft. If you're not going a thrower or thrower counter pick brawlers that are tanky enough to shrug off some damage to create space, fast enough to close distance against throwers, or good wall peekers. Tanks/wall peekers good at playing around right lane. Longer range on left lane.

bridge too far.tips: Long range or abilities to go on water will win lanes easily. Ensure you have at least two brawlers who can deal a lot of damage to the safe.

shooting star.tips: Run snipers. If enemy has a thrower make sure you have a long range assassin or your own thrower. Just draft in a way that doesn't leave you vulernable to 6th pick thrower.

ring of fire.tips: Have a versatile brawler to create pressure or pick off kills, as well as a sneaky brawler to set up a spawn trap. Long range or brawlers that greatly benefit from their supers are appreciated due to the open map and forced interaction around zone.

backyard bowl.tips: Use `/event` command to see more info about melodie challenge. This is temporarily set to melodie challenge

belles rock.tips: Map control is very strong, you can move up to the middle and force enemy to deal with the closing gas. First picks are generally squishy and long ranged, so last picks are assassins or controllers that deal well into them.

out in the open.tips: Having control of the middle usually leads to winning, either find brawlers that can confirm/initiate kills to push enemies back or have water brawlers/wall break to have multiple paths out of spawn. Last picks aren't as worrying.

pinball dreams.tips: Throwers and wall breakers are really strong first picks. Later in draft go for damage dealers or assassins when you know it's safer. Have at least one high dps brawler in draft to avoid getting counterpicked.

double swoosh.tips: Sneaky map, don't get caught lacking by being cautious with scouting and vision gear.

hideout.tips: Run snipers unless you're playing against pros. Other good classes are assassins (Mortis) and long range supports (8-Bit, R-T). Wall break negates throwers and chanes draft a lot.

center stage.tips: Team comp should have a bush scouter and tank counter (weak dps/counters leave you vulnerable to tank last pick). Vision gear great on a lot of odd brawlers (lou, otis).

safe zone.tips: Longer range/sniper brawler in middle to win engagement, aggressive brawler on the left, "cleanup" brawler on the right. Draft plays out similar to other Heist maps.

pit stop.tips: Complete base race. 1 defender + 2 rush. Angelo not good until high elo

dueling beetles.tips: Lots of walls for turrets and throwers. Aggressive brawlers and supports are also good at holding zone.

split.tips: Two down right, 1 down left. Don't break open right unless thrower, break open left.

canal grande.tips: Water walking is op. Generic snipers are not that good, throwers and last pick takes run draft. Want a brawler that is generically good at cleaning up messes, thrower that won't die to aggro, and a tank or something aggressive. Controlling middle grass is important.

sneaky fields.tips: Abuse Vision gear on brawlers that aren't tanks. Lot of strong early picks (typical brawlball fare), so tanks/aggro are usually later picks.

hard rock mine.tips: Focus on getting a good lane brawler (Surge, Rico, Ruffs, etc) as there are a lot of good middle map brawlers.

kaboom canyon.tips: Similar meta brawlers as Safe Zone and Heist in general. Get two solid DPS brawlers to play aggressive, then a cleanup brawler to establish map control.

hot potato.tips: BASE RACE. You need to properly access which opponents to ignore or defend on the safe. Make sure you have two aggressive damage dealing brawlers and a "cleanup" to defend and still deal damage on the safe. Do not control the map.

parallel plays.tips: Left zone needs defensive brawlers like throwers, high DPS, or brawlers that can charge strong supers. Middle range brawler can pinch lanes to secure either zone. Right zone will be aggressive with assassins or tanks.

open business.tips: Topsy-turvy draft with throwers and tanks. Cover your bases in draft to make sure nothing can unexpectedly throw you off.

goldarm gulch.tips: Consider trying different lane strategies or being aware of the enemy doing them. Sometimes you can send someone to sneak down right lane, or you triple stack left bush side and work your way horizontally. Lots of walls and people grouping up so use brawlers that benefit/punish those factors.

flaring phoenix.tips: Two people in middle, then another brawler left. Usually you want a thrower on the left but if there is an assassin consider stacking same lane. High health is good when gas closes in, counter throwers with your own or an aggressive brawler.

acute angle.tips: Good mid can setup spawn trap

undermine.tips: Get a sniper in mid and then anti agro, assassin, scout brawler, or wall peaker in bushes. If skill issue in bushes double up in mid(do not triple stack) for more pressure or pinching

penalty kick.tips: Throwers are OP (except for Moe and Kenji). Best throwers are Barley and Larry & Lawrie so use them or ban them. Very easy to get away with random nonsense so make sure you have a good tank counter as well.

snake prarie.tips: Rush in enemy with tanks or have better vision. Group up to be able to get revenge kills (not close enough for one enemy to teamwipe though). Vision gear runs this map.
